# Skill-creator iteration workspaces are committed for the audit trail
# (per the skill-creator convention that iteration trees are evidence,
# not throwaways), but the contents are autonomous-agent output and
# generated reports — not subject to ordinary code review. Mark them
# `linguist-generated` so GitHub's diff viewer collapses them by
# default, language stats ignore them, and PR-review bots (Copilot et
# al.) skip them.
#
# What is NOT marked here (so it stays reviewable):
# - the SKILL.md, evals/evals.json, and evals/grade.py source files
# - evals/fixtures/* (the gate-tripping spec designs and scaffold
#   templates — these are authored, reviewed artifacts)
#
# What IS marked here:
# - per-run outputs (the agent-implemented Go package + verify.log)
# - per-run grading.json / timing.json
# - eval_metadata.json (duplicates evals.json content)
# - aggregated benchmark.json / benchmark.md
# - the static review.html viewer
# - feedback.json from the review viewer
# - skill snapshots taken at the start of each iteration

**/iteration-*/eval-*/*/run-1/outputs/**             linguist-generated=true
**/iteration-*/eval-*/*/run-1/grading.json           linguist-generated=true
**/iteration-*/eval-*/*/run-1/timing.json            linguist-generated=true
**/iteration-*/eval-*/eval_metadata.json             linguist-generated=true
**/iteration-*/benchmark.json                        linguist-generated=true
**/iteration-*/benchmark.md                          linguist-generated=true
**/iteration-*/review.html                           linguist-generated=true
**/iteration-*/feedback.json                         linguist-generated=true
**/iteration-*/skill-snapshot/**                     linguist-generated=true
**/skill-snapshot-iteration-*/**                     linguist-generated=true
